  "riddle": "1. Unearth the name of the media visionary who presides over an influential South African broadcasting establishment. What is the institution he chairs?\n\n2. From the context of maritime operations, discover the height above sea level at Maritime New Zealand. What is that elevation in meters?\n\n3. Amidst the cultural resources of Maritime New Zealand, how many libraries can you find in close proximity? Count them up!\n\n4. Take the elevation you discovered in clue 2 and the number of libraries from clue 3; compute the absolute difference between them. What does that give you?\n\n5. There exists a page that reveals a prominent South African broadcasting channel. Can you pinpoint where its headquarters are located?\n\n6. In the name of the headquarters from clue 5, what is the alphabetical position of its first letter? (Remember, A=1, B=2...)\n\n7. With insight into this nation's media landscape, seek out the total population of the land where the sun shines on the Rainbow Nation. What's the figure?\n\n8. A colossal conglomerate reshaping the media realm in South Africa has a founding year etched in its history. What year was it established?\n\n9. Take the results from clues 3 and 4 to compute the absolute difference between them, followed by a modulo operation with 10. What number do you find? Remember, this is a single digit answer.",
